# DO operator specs — never commit

DigitalOcean App Platform spec **exports** contain encrypted secrets (`EV[1:...]`) and sometimes plaintext keys. They must stay **local and gitignored**.

## Blocked paths (never `git add` / commit)

| File | Source |
|------|--------|
| `admin-fe-spec.yaml` | `doctl apps spec get` (admin frontend) |
| `internal-write-api-spec.yaml` | `doctl apps spec get` (write API) |
| `chat-rag-spec.yaml` | `doctl apps spec get` (chat-rag backend) |

Also never commit: `prod.env`, `.env`, `.deploy-keys.local`.

## Use instead

| Need | Location |
|------|----------|
| Deployable app shape (no secret values) | `infra/do/*.yaml` — `type: SECRET` placeholders only |
| Runtime secrets for smokes / deploy | `prod.env` (gitignored); export `VECINITA_STAGING_INTERNAL_API_KEY` etc. |
| Live spec reference | Export to repo-root `*-spec.yaml` locally; do not push |

```bash
# Local export only (output is gitignored)
doctl apps spec get <app-id> -o yaml > admin-fe-spec.yaml
```

## Agent rules

- Do **not** create, edit, or stage root `*-spec.yaml` exports in commits.
- Do **not** paste `EV[1:...]` blobs or API keys into tracked files (`infra/do`, docs, workflows).
- If the user asks to commit operator specs, refuse and point to `infra/do/` + `prod.env`.
- If files were staged by mistake: `git rm --cached admin-fe-spec.yaml internal-write-api-spec.yaml chat-rag-spec.yaml` — do not use history rewrite unless they were already pushed.

## CI guard

`scripts/check_no_operator_specs_tracked.sh` fails if any blocked path is tracked. Run before PR:

```bash
bash scripts/check_no_operator_specs_tracked.sh
```

See `docs/deploy-report.md` §Operator spec files.
